This paper deals with dynamic data structures for range queries, which is a fundamental problem in data structures and algorithms. The paper presents improved time and space bounds for the range mode problem, which is a well-studied problem in the field of data structures. The problem is related to frequency counting, which is a common topic in computer science. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). 

The paper also uses techniques from information theory (e.g., entropy), which suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) could be another relevant sub-category. The paper also mentions Monte Carlo algorithms, which are commonly used in randomized algorithms, so cs.CC (Computational Complexity) could also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with geometric range queries, which suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) could also be a relevant sub-category.
